<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-16T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/1189: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jordan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-16T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 16,
                                        1922—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>4. Your despatch 564, January 4, 1921 [<hi rend="italic">1922</hi>].</p>
                        <p>Inform Haitian Government in reply to its memorandum to you, dated
                            December 30th, that Department cannot take into consideration any
                            suggestion questioning validity of the Protocol, which this Government
                            considers to be in full force and effect, and must stand upon its
                            suggestion that authorization be sent to the Financial Adviser to
                            undertake formal negotiations for a loan.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>